    public static enum RxTableWithMovableRecordControls.TableActionEnum
extends java.lang.Enum<RxTableWithMovableRecordControls.TableActionEnum>
    An enumeration of the available record manipulation actions on a RxTableWithMovableRecordControls. Each action either performs or facilitates an activity; see individual enum constants for more information: ADD_RECORD; REMOVE_RECORD; MOVE_RECORD_TO_TOP; MOVE_RECORD_UP; MOVE_RECORD_DOWN; MOVE_RECORD_TO_BOTTOM
    Author:
    Kevin J. Burns

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • ADD_RECORD

        public static final RxTableWithMovableRecordControls.TableActionEnum ADD_RECORD
        This action facilitates the adding of a record. When invoked, tells an external listener that the user has called for a record to be added to the list. To place an add request listener on a table widget, use the following steps:
        1. Create an AddRequestListener. You will pass this object in step 3.
        2. Call RxTableWithMovableRecordControls.getTable().
        3. On the resultant object, call RxTableWithAddedRecords.addAddRecordListener(com.gmail.at.kevinburnseit.rxtable.RxTableWithAddedRecords.AddRequestListener) with the listener created in step 1.
        4. When the user requests an add, your listener will be notified. It is your listener's responsibility to actually add the record.

      • REMOVE_RECORD

        public static final RxTableWithMovableRecordControls.TableActionEnum REMOVE_RECORD
        This action facilitates the deletion of a record. When invoked, tells an external listener that the user has called for a record to be deleted from the list. To place a remove request listener on a table widget, use the following steps:
        1. Create an RemoveRequestListener. You will pass this object in step 3.
        2. Call RxTableWithMovableRecordControls.getTable().
        3. On the resultant object, call RxTableWithAddedRecords.addRemoveListener(com.gmail.at.kevinburnseit.rxtable.RxTableWithAddedRecords.RemoveRequestListener) with the listener created in step 1.
        4. When the user requests a delete, your listener will be notified. It is your listener's responsibility to actually delete the record.

      • MOVE_RECORD_TO_TOP

        public static final RxTableWithMovableRecordControls.TableActionEnum MOVE_RECORD_TO_TOP
        This action performs a change on the data model. No external code is necessary to complete the change. When invoked, the selected record is moved to the top (beginning) of the list--that is, its new index is zero.

      • MOVE_RECORD_UP

        public static final RxTableWithMovableRecordControls.TableActionEnum MOVE_RECORD_UP
        This action performs a change on the data model. No external code is necessary to complete the change. When invoked, the selected record is moved up one slot in the index--that is, its index is reduced by one.

      • MOVE_RECORD_DOWN

        public static final RxTableWithMovableRecordControls.TableActionEnum MOVE_RECORD_DOWN
        This action performs a change on the data model. No external code is necessary to complete the change. When invoked, the selected record is moved down one slot in the index--that is, its index is increased by one.

      • MOVE_RECORD_TO_BOTTOM

        public static final RxTableWithMovableRecordControls.TableActionEnum MOVE_RECORD_TO_BOTTOM
        This action performs a change on the data model. No external code is necessary to complete the change. When invoked, the selected record is moved to the bottom (end) of the list.
